"title": "6662: freedom, abuse of Christian",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6662: freedom, abuse of christian",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Although Christians have been set free from condemnation by grace, they remain under an obligation to be obedient to God. Abuses of Christian freedom result from a failure to take responsibilities towards God seriously.</p>\n<h2>Christian freedom can be abused</h2>\n<h3>Believers are freed from condemnation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:1\">ROM 8:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:8-Isa50:9\">ISA 50:8–50:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:33-Rom8:39\">ROM 8:33–8:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:22\">COL 1:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:5\">REV 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>Sin need not enslave believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:34-John8:36\">JHN 8:34–8:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:16-Rom6:18\">ROM 6:16–6:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:14-Rom7:25\">ROM 7:14–7:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:22-1Cor7:23\">1CO 7:22–7:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:19\">2PE 2:19</a></p>\n<h3>Believers must resist sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:12\">ROM 6:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:14\">ROM 6:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:1-Heb12:2\">HEB 12:1–12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:16-1John5:18\">1JN 5:16–5:18</a></p>\n<h3>The false idea that grace gives believers the freedom to sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:1-Rom6:2\">ROM 6:1–6:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:15\">ROM 6:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:5-Rom3:8\">ROM 3:5–3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:23\">1CO 10:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:17-Gal2:21\">GAL 2:17–2:21</a></p>\n<h2>The dangers of abusing Christian freedom</h2>\n<h3>Becoming a stumbling-block to others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:9-1Cor8:12\">1CO 8:9–8:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:1-Rom15:3\">ROM 15:1–15:3</a></p>\n<h3>Indulging oneself</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:13\">GAL 5:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:1-Rom14:18\">ROM 14:1–14:18</a></p>\n<h3>Using freedom to cover up evil</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:16\">1PE 2:16</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Examples of abuse of Christian freedom</h2>\n<h3>Falling back into deliberate sin</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:1-Rom6:2\">ROM 6:1–6:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:1\">HEB 12:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:6\">1JN 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:16-1John5:18\">1JN 5:16–5:18</a></p>\n<h3>Disobedience towards God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:4\">1JN 3:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:6\">2CO 10:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:6\">EPH 5:6</a></p>\n<h3>Selfishness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:17\">1JN 3:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:32-Luke6:34\">LUK 6:32–6:34</a></p>\n<h3>Eating food sacrificed to idols</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:1-1Cor8:13\">1CO 8:1–8:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:14\">REV 2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:20\">REV 2:20</a></p>",
